{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HK7A7ukLCo4R2Hin2VSpW9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1‚Üí// Package runcontext provides a shared key-value store (context.json) for\n     2‚Üí// passing metadata between workflow steps within a single run.\n     3‚Üípackage runcontext\n     4‚Üí\n     5‚Üíimport (\n     6‚Üí\t\"encoding/json\"\n     7‚Üí\t\"fmt\"\n     8‚Üí\t\"os\"\n     9‚Üí\t\"path/filepath\"\n    10‚Üí\t\"sync\"\n    11‚Üí)\n    12‚Üí\n    13‚Üí// ContextPath returns the path to context.json for a given project and run ID.\n    14‚Üífunc ContextPath(projectDir, runID string) string {\n    15‚Üí\treturn filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"context.json\")\n    16‚Üí}\n    17‚Üí\n    18‚Üí// mu serialises concurrent reads/writes within the same process.\n    19‚Üívar mu sync.Mutex\n    20‚Üí\n    21‚Üí// Get retrieves a value from the run's context store.\n    22‚Üí// Returns (\"\", false, nil) if the key does not exist.\n    23‚Üífunc Get(projectDir, runID, key string) (string, bool, error) {\n    24‚Üí\tmu.Lock()\n    25‚Üí\tdefer mu.Unlock()\n    26‚Üí\n    27‚Üí\tm, err := load(ContextPath(projectDir, runID))\n    28‚Üí\tif err != nil {\n    29‚Üí\t\treturn \"\", false, err\n    30‚Üí\t}\n    31‚Üí\tv, ok := m[key]\n    32‚Üí\treturn v, ok, nil\n    33‚Üí}\n    34‚Üí\n    35‚Üí// Set writes a key-value pair to the run's context store, creating the file\n    36‚Üí// and parent directories if necessary.\n    37‚Üífunc Set(projectDir, runID, key, value string) error {\n    38‚Üí\tmu.Lock()\n    39‚Üí\tdefer mu.Unlock()\n    40‚Üí\n    41‚Üí\tpath := ContextPath(projectDir, runID)\n    42‚Üí\n    43‚Üí\tif err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(path), 0755); err != nil {\n    44‚Üí\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating context directory: %w\", err)\n    45‚Üí\t}\n    46‚Üí\n    47‚Üí\tm, err := load(path)\n    48‚Üí\tif err != nil {\n    49‚Üí\t\treturn err\n    50‚Üí\t}\n    51‚Üí\tm[key] = value\n    52‚Üí\treturn save(path, m)\n    53‚Üí}\n    54‚Üí\n    55‚Üí// load reads the context map from disk. Returns an empty map if the file does\n    56‚Üí// not exist.\n    57‚Üífunc load(path string) (map[string]string, error) {\n    58‚Üí\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n    59‚Üí\tif err != nil {\n    60‚Üí\t\tif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n    61‚Üí\t\t\treturn make(map[string]string), nil\n    62‚Üí\t\t}\n    63‚Üí\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading context file: %w\", err)\n    64‚Üí\t}\n    65‚Üí\tvar m map[string]string\n    66‚Üí\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &m); err != nil {\n    67‚Üí\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing context file: %w\", err)\n    68‚Üí\t}\n    69‚Üí\treturn m, nil\n    70‚Üí}\n    71‚Üí\n    72‚Üí// save writes the context map to disk as indented JSON.\n    73‚Üífunc save(path string, m map[string]string) error {\n    74‚Üí\tdata, err := json.MarshalIndent(m, \"\", \"  \")\n    75‚Üí\tif err != nil {\n    76‚Üí\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"encoding context: %w\", err)\n    77‚Üí\t}\n    78‚Üí\tdata = append(data, '\\n')\n    79‚Üí\tif err := os.WriteFile(path, data, 0644); err != nil {\n    80‚Üí\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"writing context file: %w\", err)\n    81‚Üí\t}\n    82‚Üí\treturn nil\n    83‚Üí}\n    84‚Üí"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24e7cbc4-6cfb-4f98-90d9-671b9018c30a","uuid":"561e064b-fdc2-4ab0-968d-8aa13a0bab51","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/runcontext/store.go","content":"// Package runcontext provides a shared key-value store (context.json) for\n// passing metadata between workflow steps within a single run.\npackage runcontext\n\nimport (\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"sync\"\n)\n\n// ContextPath returns the path to context.json for a given project and run ID.\nfunc ContextPath(projectDir, runID string) string {\n\treturn filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"context.json\")\n}\n\n// mu serialises concurrent reads/writes within the same process.\nvar mu sync.Mutex\n\n// Get retrieves a value from the run's context store.\n// Returns (\"\", false, nil) if the key does not exist.\nfunc Get(projectDir, runID, key string) (string, bool, error) {\n\tmu.Lock()\n\tdefer mu.Unlock()\n\n\tm, err := load(ContextPath(projectDir, runID))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", false, err\n\t}\n\tv, ok := m[key]\n\treturn v, ok, nil\n}\n\n// Set writes a key-value pair to the run's context store, creating the file\n// and parent directories if necessary.\nfunc Set(projectDir, runID, key, value string) error {\n\tmu.Lock()\n\tdefer mu.Unlock()\n\n\tpath := ContextPath(projectDir, runID)\n\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(path), 0755); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating context directory: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tm, err := load(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tm[key] = value\n\treturn save(path, m)\n}\n\n// load reads the context map from disk. Returns an empty map if the file does\n// not exist.\nfunc load(path string) (map[string]string, error) {\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\treturn make(map[string]string), nil\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading context file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tvar m map[string]string\n\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &m); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing context file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn m, nil\n}\n\n// save writes the context map to disk as indented JSON.\nfunc save(path string, m map[string]string) error {\n\tdata, err := json.MarshalIndent(m, \"\", \"  \")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"encoding context: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tdata = append(data, '\\n')\n\tif err := os.WriteFile(path, data, 0644); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"writing context file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EpJQCsKapYNLhirGe9zSJo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. I need to update USAGE.md in three places:\n\n1. **Host Step Environment Variables table** (line 346): Add `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`\n2. **CLI Reference**: Add `cloche get` and `cloche set` commands\n3. **Project Layout** (line 539): Add `context.json` to the `<run-id>/` directory listing\n\nLet me also consider adding a section about the Run Context Store concept. Looking at the structure of USAGE.md, the most natural places are:\n\n1. After the \"Host Step Environment Variables\" and \"Container Environment Variables\" sections, or as a new section explaining the context store\n\n\n2. In the CLI Reference section for the new commands\n\nNow I'll make these edits.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1408,"cache_read_input_tokens":26723,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1408},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24e7cbc4-6cfb-4f98-90d9-671b9018c30a","uuid":"17145e92-becb-45a2-87e6-93f9827167f7"}
